The paper focuses on distributed data management for Semantic Web data, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The use of machine-interpretable semantic descriptions and RDF data also suggests a connection to natural language processing and information retrieval (cs.DL, cs.IR). Finally, the comparison of cloud computing technologies with traditional relational database clustering technologies suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
